      "rationale": "Relative hemolysis index RH is the FDA-recognised surrogate endpoint for pump-induced haemolysis in CPB devices. RH < 1 criterion directly maps to the regulatory submission acceptance threshold. QoI is mechanistically connected to erythrocyte damage via power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.), which has been validated against clinical data in peer-reviewed literature."
    },
