    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Mesh convergence GCI 1.3%, output comparison within combined uncertainty at all operating points, turbulence model sensitivity characterised at ±3.4% RH. The 6 non-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 4. Total predictive uncertainty budget (RSS combination of numerical, input, and model-form contributions) yields 95% confidence interval of ±0.14 RH units, which does not alter the RH < 1 accept/reject decision at any of the 5 operating points. Assessment team concludes the CFD model has sufficient credibility for the stated COU.",
